        "subject": "LU-4971 ldlm: drop redundant ibits lock interoperability check",
        "message": "LU-4971 ldlm: drop redundant ibits lock interoperability check\n\nIn very old release (older than Lustre-1.8), if the client talks with\nthe server that does not support ibits lock, then the client needs to\nconvert it as plain lock. Such interoperability check and convertion\nis out of date for a long time. Drop it.\n\nThis patch is back-ported from the following one:\nLustre-commit: a1ef13bca025e09e10ce2d6e007013d0e187e6eb\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/11004\n\nTest-Parameters: alwaysuploadlogs envdefinitions=ONLY=240 \\\nossjob=lustre-b2_4 mdsjob=lustre-b2_4 ossbuildno=73 mdsbuildno=73 \\\ntestlist=sanity\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I629f00a04c78c65ddb843e279768d686408cbcbd\n"
      },
